EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to motor clubs; revising certain information which
a motor club is required to provide to its members;
revising certain qualifications for a license as a club
agent; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires every motor club to furnish to its members certain
2 information about the address of the motor club, including the exact location of: (1)
3 the home office of the motor club; and (2) the usual place of business of the motor
4 club in this State. (NRS 696A.190) Section 1 of this bill removes the requirement
5 for a motor club to provide information about the usual place of business of the
6 motor club in this State. Existing law requires, for an individual who is not a
7 resident of this State to be licensed as a club agent, that the state in which the
8 individual resides also permits a resident of this State to act as a club agent. (NRS
9 696A.280) Section 2 of this bill additionally authorizes an individual who is not a
10 resident of this State to be licensed as a club agent if the state in which the
11 individual resides does not require a license to act as a club agent.
